&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical Support Division&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;QMC Campus, Main Theatres&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full time Theatre Practitioner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a HCPC registered ODP or a first level Registered Nurse with the NMC? Would you like the challenge of scrubbing for complex technical cases within a supportive well led team or providing skilled support to our Anaesthetists? An exciting opportunity has arisen for us to recruit a Band 5 Theatre Practitioner to strengthen our Emergency Team based at QMC. We practice multi-skilling and are looking to recruit a dynamic Practitioner who wishes to develop their practice in either Anaesthesia and/or surgical scrub support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be joining a pro-active, dynamic team of nurses and ODP’s, who offer the best standards of perioperative care. Every day is different - challenging but rewarding. We pride ourselves on team work, learning and being forward thinking.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Expectations are to deliver a high quality service, with patient safety a priority. You should be able to demonstrate effective team working and work to the highest standards of evidence based practice. A sense of humour and pride in your job is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can support you to develop your own practice through exposure to complex techniques quite unique to Emergency anaesthetics/surgery. We offer the anaesthetic course for registered nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NUH is a Major Trauma Centre offering fantastic support to a diverse range of students and learners and therefore the successful applicant should either hold or be willing to work towards a level three mentorship qualification.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will participate in the current Main Theatre rota which includes out of hours work, nights and weekend shifts. There is a commitment to Bank Holiday work and on-calls.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameThomas BrownAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thomas.brown@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
